observations.recommendation:
We recommended Management to:
direct the Accounting Office and General Services Office to determine the difference of their records and make necessary adjustments if any, and;
require the Inventory Committee to convene and strategize the conduct of physical count of all Properties Plant and Equipment of the municipality to present a more realistic report;

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to:
Direct the Municipal Engineering Office to submit disbursement vouchers together with copies of Certificate of Completion/Statement of Work Accomplished (SWA) on completed projects to the Municipal Accountant for processing and proper recording in the books of accounts;
Advise the Municipal Accountant to reclassify completed projects into the appropriate asset account based on the submitted documents by the Municipal Engineering Office to its related PPE, and;
Recognize the related depreciation expense and accumulated depreciation for the said projects from the time they were available for use.

We hereby recommended management to:
refrain from charging items not in accordance with the creation of the Trust Fund, and;
strictly follow the Work and Financial Plan of the project/program/activities to attain the program/project/activities ultimate purpose.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to direct the concerned offices to:
ensure that all projects/programs/activities undertaken by the Municipality, irrespective of funding sources, be reported quarterly, and;
direct all offices involved in the implementation, monitoring and reporting to coordinate with its other so that accurate and reliable information will be attained.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to direct the MEO, MAO and other concerned departments to:
closely monitor and ensure economic and efficient implementation of all projects under the pertinent National Programs by virtue of the funds transfer received from the National Government agencies, and;
submit the required documents to our office (approved extension letter, extra work order, etc.), as the case maybe, relative to the delays/ suspensions/extensions of the above-cited projects; and,

We recommended management to:
Stop the grant of registration fess of in excess of the P2,000.00 limitation per day per participant for conventions, meetings, seminars and trainings conducted by NGOs and private institutions, as provided by under National Budget Circular No. 563, otherwise the excess shall be shouldered by the participant;
Adhere with the provisions of Executive Order No. 298 in the grant of traveling expenses for attendance of officials to conventions, meetings and conferences by submitting the required documentary requirements;
Require the concerned officials and employees to refund their excess claims as shown above considering the requirements that any amount in excess of the prescribed rate shall be at the expense of the participants and;
Justify why are the claims were charged against the Disaster funds of the municipality and not in the MOOE.

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer to:
Coordinate with the Municipal Assessor’s Office and devise a comprehensive strategy primarily focused on:
updating the taxpayers’ profile in the computer program;
identifying the owners of the problematic properties and confer with them on how to legally divide their properties so that assessment will be made to each property; and
the collection of delinquent property taxes to substantially reduce the outstanding amount of delinquencies;
Request sufficient funding for plantilla position and for other needs of the office to facilitate effective property tax collection, monitoring, and assessment.

We recommended the following:

Submit justification letter on the above-noted deficiencies;

Allocate 1% of the IRA for the strengthening of the LCPC and implementation of PPAs and;

Establish and/or prepare Council’s Annual Work and Financial Plan, Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC), Local Investment Plan for Children (LIPC) and prepare Municipal CPC Annual Report.

